        "<p>away as easily as you could carry a feather.</p>\n<p>It was very dark, and the wind howled horribly around her, but Dorothy</p>\n<p>found she was riding quite easily.</p>\n<p>After the first few whirls around,</p>\n<p>and one other time when the house tipped badly, she felt as if she were</p>\n<p>being rocked gently, like a baby in a cradle.</p>\n<p>Toto did not like it.</p>\n",
